title: No. 5 Bulldogs Skate to Series Stalemate
text:
No. 5 Bulldogs Skate to Series Stalemate 
By Norman Seawright III October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 10:40 PM CDT 
South Bend, IN (NNCNOW.com) -- The University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team came up with another tie game against Notre Dame. 
Two goals from Tony Cameranesi and a late one from Neal Pionk kept the Bulldogs in the game (the Irish got as far as two goals ahead), while 27 saves by Kasimir Kaskisuo helped prevent any further scoring.
